This paper deals with robotic grasping, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves 3D segmentation and geometric and semantic shape characteristics, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of active learning and local replanning involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves building bijective contact mapping, which is related to graph theory and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with robotic manipulation, which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
